---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
import CodeBlock from "../../components/CodeBlock.astro";
import Callout from "../../components/Callout.astro";

const mainEntry = `import { WompiClient, WompiRequest, type WompiRequestConfig } from "@pulgueta/wompi";`;

const clientEntry = `import { WompiClient } from "@pulgueta/wompi/client";`;

const typesEntry = `import type {
  WompiClientOptions,
  Result,
  Transaction,
  TransactionStatus,
  CreateTransactionInput,
  PaymentLink,
  CreatePaymentLinkInput,
  PaymentSource,
  CardToken,
  NequiToken,
  Merchant,
  FinancialInstitution,
} from "@pulgueta/wompi/types";`;

const schemasEntry = `import {
  CreateTransactionInputSchema,
  TokenizeCardInputSchema,
  CreatePaymentLinkInputSchema,
} from "@pulgueta/wompi/schemas";

// Validate an incoming form body before passing it to the SDK.
const parsed = CreateTransactionInputSchema.safeParse(req.body);
if (!parsed.success) return res.status(400).json(parsed.error.flatten());`;

const errorsEntry = `import {
  WompiError,
  WompiNotFoundError,
  WompiValidationError,
  WompiRequestError,
} from "@pulgueta/wompi/errors";`;

const serverEntry = `import { getSignatureKey } from "@pulgueta/wompi/server";`;
---

<DocsLayout
  section="Reference"
  title="Package exports"
  description="Every entry point @pulgueta/wompi ships and what's behind it."
>
  <p>
    The package is published as ESM and CJS with separate type declarations for each subpath. Pull
    in only the entry you need — the others stay out of your bundle.
  </p>

  <h2 id="main">
    <code>@pulgueta/wompi</code>
  </h2>
  <p>
    The default entry. Re-exports the client and the lower-level request primitive.
  </p>
  <CodeBlock code={mainEntry} lang="ts" />
  <ul>
    <li><code>WompiClient</code> — the high-level client constructed in every other doc page.</li>
    <li><code>WompiRequest</code> — the base class wrapping <code>fetch</code> + Zod parsing. Use it directly only when you need to call an endpoint the SDK hasn't covered yet.</li>
    <li><code>WompiRequestConfig</code> (alias: <code>BaseConfig</code>) — the constructor options type.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="client">
    <code>@pulgueta/wompi/client</code>
  </h2>
  <p>
    Just the <code>WompiClient</code> class. Use this entry if you want to skip importing
    <code>WompiRequest</code> and its types.
  </p>
  <CodeBlock code={clientEntry} lang="ts" />

  <h2 id="types">
    <code>@pulgueta/wompi/types</code>
  </h2>
  <p>
    Every typed shape derived from the Zod schemas — return types, input types, enums and union
    types — without pulling Zod itself into your bundle.
  </p>
  <CodeBlock code={typesEntry} lang="ts" />

  <Callout type="tip" title="Typed enums">
    <code>TransactionStatus</code>, <code>PaymentMethodType</code> and <code>LegalIdType</code>
    are string literal unions — perfect for narrowing in <code>switch</code> statements without
    importing the schema.
  </Callout>

  <h2 id="schemas">
    <code>@pulgueta/wompi/schemas</code>
  </h2>
  <p>
    The raw Zod schemas. Pair them with your own routing layer to validate request bodies before
    they hit the SDK.
  </p>
  <CodeBlock code={schemasEntry} lang="ts" />

  <h2 id="errors">
    <code>@pulgueta/wompi/errors</code>
  </h2>
  <p>
    The error subclasses, for when you'd rather <code>instanceof</code>-check than branch on
    <code>error.type</code>.
  </p>
  <CodeBlock code={errorsEntry} lang="ts" />

  <p>
    See <a href="/docs/error-handling">Error handling</a> for a comparison of both styles.
  </p>

  <h2 id="server">
    <code>@pulgueta/wompi/server</code>
  </h2>
  <p>
    The server-only helpers. Currently houses <code>getSignatureKey</code>, the integrity
    signature builder. Kept in its own entry so the client bundle stays free of crypto code.
  </p>
  <CodeBlock code={serverEntry} lang="ts" />

  <h2 id="summary">Subpath summary</h2>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Subpath</th><th>Exports</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>.</code></td><td><code>WompiClient</code>, <code>WompiRequest</code>, types</td><td>The default entry.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>./client</code></td><td><code>WompiClient</code></td><td>Smallest possible import for the high-level client.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>./types</code></td><td>Every <code>z.output&lt;…&gt;</code> type</td><td>Zero-runtime — type-only.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>./schemas</code></td><td>Every Zod schema</td><td>For server-side validation layers.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>./errors</code></td><td>Error subclasses</td><td>For <code>instanceof</code> branching.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>./server</code></td><td><code>getSignatureKey</code></td><td>Web Crypto, server-only.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</DocsLayout>
